         "2",
         "4731250",
         "2024-06-24T16:56:05Z",
         "9",
         "HTOC Org",
         "https://hvs.threatconnect.com/#/details/indicators/4731250",
         "Address",
         "2025-09-30T12:15:51Z",
         "3.0",
         "6.0",
         "A Citrix Password Spray campaign was observed with an affiliate of Health-ISAC on June 21, 2024. A large non-profit healthcare system experienced a password spray attack by an unknown threat actor. This measure will effectively block the threat actor at the firewall level, preventing any authentication attempts from reaching the Citrix NetScalers. Health-ISAC shared these IOCs to increase awareness in Healthcare sector. Organizations are encouraged to ingest these IOCs in their Threat Intelligen",
         "False",
         "True",
         "False",
         "https://hvs.threatconnect.com/auth/indicators/details/address.xhtml?address=108.165.219.0&owner=HTOC+Org",
         "[{'id': 277223, 'name': 'Alert ID: 0599ab6', 'lastUsed': '2024-06-24T00:00:00Z'}, {'id': 277222, 'name': 'Citrix Netscaler', 'lastUsed': '2025-05-28T05:43:36Z'}, {'id': 245130, 'name': 'TLP: AMBER', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-04T16:49:49Z'}, {'id': 214752, 'name': 'Health-ISAC', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-04T16:49:49Z'}, {'id': 38555, 'name': 'Brute Force: Password Spraying', 'description': 'Adversaries may use a single or small list of commonly used passwords against many different accounts to attempt to acquire valid account credentials. Password spraying uses one password (e.g. \\'Password01\\'), or a small list of commonly used passwords, that may match the complexity policy of the domain. Logins are attempted with that password against many different accounts on a network to avoid account lockouts that would normally occur when brute forcing a single account with many passwords. (Citation: BlackHillsInfosec Password Spraying)\\n\\nTypically, management services over commonly used ports are used when password spraying. Commonly targeted services include the following:\\n\\n* SSH (22/TCP)\\n* Telnet (23/TCP)\\n* FTP (21/TCP)\\n* NetBIOS / SMB / Samba (139/TCP & 445/TCP)\\n* LDAP (389/TCP)\\n* Kerberos (88/TCP)\\n* RDP / Terminal Services (3389/TCP)\\n* HTTP/HTTP Management Services (80/TCP & 443/TCP)\\n* MSSQL (1433/TCP)\\n* Oracle (1521/TCP)\\n* MySQL (3306/TCP)\\n* VNC (5900/TCP)\\n\\nIn addition to management services, adversaries may \"target single sign-on (SSO) and cloud-based applications utilizing federated authentication protocols,\" as well as externally facing email applications, such as Office 365.(Citation: US-CERT TA18-068A 2018)\\n\\nIn default environments, LDAP and Kerberos connection attempts are less likely to trigger events over SMB, which creates Windows \"logon failure\" event ID 4625.', 'lastUsed': '2025-07-17T14:59:26Z', 'techniqueId': 'T1110.003', 'tactics': {'data': ['Credential Access'], 'count': 1}, 'platforms': {'data': ['Containers', 'IaaS', 'Identity Provider', 'Linux', 'Network Devices', 'Office Suite', 'SaaS', 'Windows', 'macOS', 'ESXi'], 'count': 10}}, {'id': 35057, 'name': 'FDA Splunk API', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-28T07:26:00Z'}, {'id': 30479, 'name': 'CMS Splunk API', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-30T03:22:32Z'}, {'id': 23586, 'name': 'IHS Splunk API', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-28T13:07:45Z'}, {'id': 23577, 'name': 'HHS Splunk API', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-29T06:30:44Z'}, {'id': 23576, 'name': 'Observed', 'lastUsed': '2025-09-30T00:00:00Z'}]",
